definition.value: An EC 1.14.11.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, 2-oxoglutarate as one donor, incorporating 1 atom each of oxygen into both donors) inhibitor that interferes with the action of hypoxia-inducible factor-proline dioxygenase (EC 1.14.11.29).
An alpha-curcumene that has R configuration at the chiral centre.
A N-glycosyl-1,2,4-triazine that is the 6-aza analogue of thymidine 5'-monophosphate.
A sulfonamide consisting of pyrimidine with methyl substituents at the 4- and 6-positions and a 4-aminobenzenesulfonamido group at the 2-position.

An L-lysine derivative in which the alpha-amino nitrogen of the amino acid has entered into amide formation with acetic acid and the epsilon-amino nitrogen carries a 1,4-dihydroxynonan-3-yl substituent. It has been synthesised by reaction of (E)-4-hydroxynon-2-enal (HNE) with N(2)-acetyl-L-lysine, the epsilon amino group of lysine reacting with the double bond function of HNE via formation of a Michael adduct.
